author: @BZK-.
text:
During my recent trip to china, i stopped by a restaurant whose gimmick is that the decor is fully themed around a romanticised old china (I believe the chain is called Nanking nights?). there were 2 masters playing traditional chinese music and i was blown away by the different note scales they used and the music also featured a lot of tuplets which i found very interesting.

It does sadden me that these masters seem to be reduced to being not much more than a novelty at a themed restaurant, but i guess it's better than the art dying out completely.
